'''''Anakin to the Rescue''''' is a children's picture book inclusive of stickers written by [[Cecilia Venn]] and illustrated by [[Chris Trevas]]. It is a '''[[Jedi Readers]] Step 2 (Grades 1-3)''' young readers publication. It depicts the events that happen while [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] is waiting to see if he can train to be a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]].

==Publisher's summary==
'''"ALWAYS HELP OTHERS."'''

In Anakin to the Rescue, Anakin is supposed to wait for Qui-Gon outside the Jedi Temple. But Anakin ''hates'' waiting! And when he and Jar Jar find a lost little boy, Anakin knows he must help him. He wants to be brave and good, just like a Jedi Knight!<ref name="Random House" />

==Plot summary==
[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], newly arrived on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] from [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], is waiting outside the [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Jedi Temple]] for [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]] to arrive with news of the [[Jedi Council/Legends|Council's]] decision about Anakin's application to join the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Order]]. Tired of waiting, he decides to walk around the neighborhood. [[Jar Jar Binks/Legends|Jar Jar Binks]] follows him in order to keep Anakin out of trouble. Before long, both beings have strayed too far and cannot see the Temple.

Suddenly, trouble comes into view when a malfunctioning [[Unidentified nanny droid (Coruscant)|nanny droid]] runs past them, leaving its charge, a boy named [[Finn (boy)|Finn]], lost and confused. Anakin, who has recently been separated from [[Shmi Skywalker Lars/Legends|his own mother]], empathizes with Finn. He determines to help catch the droid and fix its programming. The slapstick chase leads Anakin, Jar Jar, and Finn through a hall of mirrors, an airbus, and a traffic intersection, where Jar Jar arouses the ire of a road-raged [[Gotal/Legends|Gotal]]. Finally, the droid becomes stuck in a garbage chute infested with [[Spider-roach/Legends|spider-roaches]] which Jar Jar finds edible. Anakin fixes the droid's crossed wires, and the droid leads them to Finn's home. [[Finn's mother]] has her droid chauffeur drive Anakin and Jar Jar back to the Temple.

Qui-Gon is waiting worriedly for Anakin at the Temple. Anakin explains what happened, and that his mother advised him to help people in distress. Qui-Gon says he understands, and that Anakin behaved like a true Jedi.

